metadata.name: Quantum Places Lost in Time #176
metadata.description:
A frozen scene from a lost dimension
An alternative of where we once were, or where we will be 
Caught in the moment and set in place
Between all states
Static pixels on a digital canvas

The path to this collection has created many alternatives lost in time themselves. It began as a study of points of light, with geometric objects in the background. The background objects developed a life of their own and then birds, and ships, made out of bezier shapes became the focal points. Then everything got lost in clouds before the collection as it stands now emerged. Aside from the published traits, many of the artifacts created on the way are still generated. For example, star fields, birds, sonars and gas bubbles. These are sometimes visible, but when they appear, it is simply by some chaotic chance.

This collection has been coded with P5js and WebGL. Half of all primary sales proceeds, and secondary royalties, are assigned to the Processing Foundation.

Press s to download a 2880 x 3840 jpeg

This work is licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial 4.0 International License.

metadata.name: Mixed Hopes #31
metadata.description:
This piece is an interpretation of the various hopes that each person might have. Accumulated into one frame. Colliding within each other.

The visual representation shows liquid-like textures with various colors that are placed together and create a mixed-imposed composition.

Press ’s’ on the live mode to save the screen capture.

Made using Hydra (https://hydra.ojack.xyz/)

Rangga Purnama Aji, 2022

metadata.name: Noises under noises #24
metadata.description:
Oscilações naturais e orgânicas influenciam nossa interpretação do meio digital. Através destas colisões artísticas e tecnológicas de diferente campos, realizo esta coleção de movimento perpetuo para o terceiro festival de criptoarte psicodélica @apupiladilatada. Entre cores e sons busco interagir e celebrar a ancestralidade da cultura psicodélica,  em "Noise under noises" levo minha interpretação do individuo como ruido em movimento e a união como uma esfera. A necessidade de perpetuar e transmitir a tradição oral, visual e sonora para continuar a colidir essas esferas e ampliar diferentes campos da arte e conhecimento. 

Feito em hydra.ojack.xyz | Fxhash | Pupila3

Marcelo Moura, 2022

metadata.name: Faux #207
metadata.description:
This project is borne out of my longstanding fascination with brushwork, and the intricate textures that can be created with a brush, some paint and a canvas. Brush strokes are simulated using many overlapping lines and given texture and depth using a custom shader. Another important aspect of this work, is the composite forms that are created by the brush strokes, which are my attempt to emulate the emphatic energy of many abstract painters that have come before me. Color palettes are named after common paint colors, based on the background color used for the palette.

Those who collect during the first tier of the Dutch Auction can claim a signed print. They will be printed on A3 Hahnemuhle Photo Rag, and shipped to the collector free of charge. More details on how to claim a print and specify the necessary shipping information will be provided via the artists twitter (@landlinesart1).

In live mode, add &size=<YOUR_PIXEL_SIZE> to change the pixel size of the image for export (Right click to save). For example, &size=4000 will set the width of the image to be 4000 pixels.

metadata.name: CRAYONS #136
metadata.description:
Sometimes we like the feeling of being citizens of the places we visit. Our senses adapt to capture in detail the signs of the environment. It is then when we begin to breathe the color that surrounds us and places us in that unique setting.

This is how this inspired collection is born and grows, the colors that enchant us as children on a sheet of paper and now serve to paint every place we visit.

The 6 color palettes of this collection aim to transport us to all those places.

Paris: Its pastel tones strolling along the Trocadero on the banks of the Seine.

Berlin: How to tell the story with color in the graffiti of the East Side Gallery and the wall.

Mexico: Its flavor is in the rainbow of its embroideries, alebrijes and altars.

Kenya: Sunrises and sunsets that impregnate the retina with the tones of the savannah.

Costa Rica: Pure life, pure green, from gentle to intense Monte Lluvioso.

Colombia: Seas of flowers flood the streets with colors and aromas celebrating the Feria De Las Flores

High-resolution png downloads are available by pressing number keys 1 (3000px), 2 (6000px), or 3 (9000px).

metadata.name: Mines #6
metadata.description:
"He found himself wondering at times, especially in the autumn, about the wild lands, and strange visions of mountains that he had never seen came into his dreams"
- J.R.R. Tolkien

Mines is an exploration of these mountains of dreams, and the ancient mechanics that shape them. The work of eons, where the landscapes we know rise and fall like ocean waves.

To know them, we must go beneath the mountain.

---
- Made with p5js
- Press “s” to save png
- Use param ?width=x to render at specific width
- Use param ?bg=true to render on full color background (instead of the default dark background)
